      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a headache, you need to be absolutely certain of what you're taking, and I'm not a doctor, so I can't give you a prescription. However, if you absolutely must self-treat, try acetaminophen, but only take a single dose, and make sure you check with your pharmacist about the exact timing with your warfarin. If the headache persists or gets worse, you need to be ready to go, because sometimes these things are more than just a simple headache.",
