      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a severe headache, you need a solid dose, and 1000mg of acetaminophen is a very high, potentially risky dose for someone on blood thinners, so I recommend starting with 500mg, but you should definitely double-check with your pharmacist first. If you want maximum effect, take 1000mg, but only once, and then monitor yourself closely for any signs of trouble. If it doesn't work, you need a different approach, not just more pills.",
      "source": "target",
